                        <title key="work_5815">Electuarium in Delectatione et Refocillatione Animae</title>
                        <rubric>Bernardus de reparatione lapsus humani</rubric>
                        <incipit>Consideranti diligentius quid sit homo, nichil probabilius occurrit quam ipsum esse animal diuinum</incipit>
                        <explicit>ex hoc mundo ad Patrem cui ...</explicit>
                        <note>unpr.; Sharpe, <title>Handlist</title> , p. 449, citing two copies, not this one; there were three more at Dover Priory in 1389.</note>
                     </msItem>
                     <msItem n="4">
